programme.title: WhatAYear F1HL: 25: Chinese GP
programme.desc: Formula One Blitz Highlights - Heineken Chinese Grand Prix. Oscar Piastri won the Chinese main race from pole position, leading a McLaren one-two finish ahead of teammate Lando Norris.

programme.title: WhatAYear F1HL: 25: Japan GP
programme.desc: Formula One Blitz Highlights - Lenovo Japanese Grand Prix. The Japanese GP was won by Max Verstappen, who fended off a race-long challenge from the two McLarens of Lando Norris and Oscar Piastri.

programme.title: WhatAYear F1HL: 25: Bahrain GP
programme.desc: Formula One Blitz Highlights - Bahrain Grand Prix. Oscar Piastri of McLaren converted his pole position to a victory, ahead of George Russell of Mercedes and Piastris teammate Lando Norris.

programme.title: WhatAYear F1HL: 25: Saudi Arabia GP
programme.desc: Formula One Blitz Highlights - STC Saudi Arabian Grand Prix. Oscar Piastri won the 2025 Saudi Arabian GP, taking the WDC lead for McLaren. Verstappen took P2 despite a 5s penalty, with Leclerc P3.

programme.title: WhatAYear F1HL: 25: Miami GP
programme.desc: Formula One Blitz Highlights - Crypto.com Miami Grand Prix. Piastri storms to victory at the 2025 Miami GP, leading a McLaren 1-2 with Norris. Russell takes third as Verstappen slips to fourth after losing the lead on lap 14.

programme.title: WhatAYear F1HL: 25: Emilia-Romagna GP
programme.desc: Formula One Blitz Highlights - AWS Gran Premio Del Made in Italy E DellEmilia-Romagna. Verstappen triumphs at Imola, winning the Emilia-Romagna GP ahead of Norris and Piastri.

programme.title: WhatAYear F1HL: 25: Monaco GP
programme.desc: Formula One Blitz Highlights - Grand Prix De Monaco. Norris won from pole, holding off Leclerc. Piastri P3. Verstappen P4 after a late tire gamble failed. Norriss win cut the title lead to 3 points in a strategic race.

programme.title: WhatAYear F1HL: 25: Spanish GP
programme.desc: Formula One Blitz Highlights - Aramco Gran Premio De Espana. Oscar Piastri controlled the race from pole position, leading a strong showing by McLaren. Lando Norris finished just a few seconds behind.

programme.title: WhatAYear F1HL: 25: Canada GP
programme.desc: Formula One Blitz Highlights - Pirelli Grand Prix Du Canada. Russell claims pole-to-flag win in Montreal, with Verstappen second and rookie Antonelli third. Russell nabbed fastest lap, McLarens Norris and Piastri collide late.

programme.title: WhatAYear F1HL: 25: Austrian GP
programme.desc: Formula One Blitz Highlights - MSC Cruises Austrian Grand Prix. Norris won at the Red Bull Ring. Piastri P2 ensured McLaren dominance on Red Bulls turf with Leclerc finishing P3.

programme.title: WhatAYear F1HL: 25: British GP
programme.desc: Formula One Blitz Highlights - Qatar Airways British Grand Prix. Norris won a wet-dry home GP. Piastri P2, with Hulkenberg a shock P3 for Sauber.

programme.title: WhatAYear F1HL: 25: Belgian GP
programme.desc: Formula One Blitz Highlights - Belgian Grand Prix. Piastri won at Spa. Norris P2, Leclerc P3. McLaren extended their Constructors lead significantly over Red Bull.

programme.title: WhatAYear F1HL: 25: Hungarian GP
programme.desc: Formula One Blitz Highlights - Lenovo Hungarian Grand Prix. Lando Norris wins for McLaren, narrowly beating his teammate Oscar Piastri in a thrilling finish, marking McLarens 200th F1 win.

programme.title: WhatAYear F1HL: 25: Netherlands GP
programme.desc: Formula One Blitz Highlights - Heineken Dutch Grand Prix. Piastri spoiled Verstappens home party with a win. Verstappen P2, Hadjar a shock P3 for RB.

programme.title: WhatAYear F1HL: 25: Italy GP
programme.desc: Formula One Blitz Highlights - Pirelli Gran Premio DItalia. Verstappen won at Monza. Norris P2, Piastri P3. Ferrari missed the home podium as Leclerc finished P4.

programme.title: WhatAYear F1HL: 25: Azerbaijan GP
programme.desc: Formula One Blitz Highlights - Qatar Airways Azerbaijan Grand Prix. Verstappen mastered the Baku streets to win from pole. Russell P2, while Carlos Sainz took a maiden Williams podium in P3.

programme.title: WhatAYear F1HL: 25: Singapore GP
programme.desc: Formula One Blitz Highlights - Singapore Airlines Singapore Grand Prix. George Russell converted pole into a brilliant win. Verstappen took P2 after holding off a fierce charge from Norris (P3).

programme.title: WhatAYear F1HL: 25: United States GP
programme.desc: Formula One Blitz Highlights - MSC Cruises United States Grand Prix. Verstappen dominated the weekend, winning both the Sprint and the Grand Prix. Norris beat Leclerc to P2 after a thrilling late-race duel.

programme.title: WhatAYear F1HL: 25: Mexico GP
programme.desc: Formula One Blitz Highlights - Gran Premio De La Ciudad De Mexico. Norris won from pole, Leclerc took P2, while Verstappen fought from P5 to P3. Rookie Ollie Bearman secured a career-best P4 for Haas.

programme.title: WhatAYear F1HL: 25: Sao Paulo GP
programme.desc: Formula One Blitz Highlights - MSC Cruises Grande Premio De Sao Paulo. Norris mastered the rain at Interlagos to win both the Sprint and Grand Prix. Kimi Antonelli took a sensational P2 for Mercedes, with Verstappen P3.

programme.title: WhatAYear F1HL: 25: Las Vegas GP
programme.desc: Formula One Blitz Highlights - Heineken Las Vegas Grand Prix. Verstappen won a cold, chaotic night race. Russell and Antonelli followed for a Mercedes 2-3. Both McLarens were disqualified for technical infringements.

programme.title: WhatAYear F1HL: 25: Qatar GP
programme.desc: Formula One Blitz Highlights - Qatar Airways Qatar Grand Prix. Verstappen won again after a McLaren strategy blunder. Piastri took P2 and Carlos Sainz scored a podium for Williams in P3.

programme.title: WhatAYear F1HL: 25: Abu Dhabi GP
programme.desc: Formula One Blitz Highlights - Etihad Airways Abu Dhabi Grand Prix. Verstappen won the race, but Norriss P3 was enough to secure the World Championship by just 2 points.

programme.title: El Clasico Legends: Ronaldinho
programme.desc: Ronaldinho. Ronaldinhos finest Clásico came on the 19th of November of 2005. Just one point separated both teams in the table, but the Brazilian proved that the gulf on the pitch was much greater.

programme.title: El Clasico Legends: Andres Iniesta
programme.desc: Andres Iniesta. Andres Iniesta Luján. A normal person that was capable of the extraordinary. A glorious career which was also built, in part, on magical performances in ElClásico.

programme.title: El Clasico Legends: James Rodríguez
programme.desc: James Rodríguez. James Rodríguez forced his way into Real Madrids history books by virtue of his footballing IQ, his magic on the ball and his ability to impress a hugely demanding fanbase.

programme.title: El Clasico Moments: BAR v RMA 18/19
programme.desc: El Clasico Moments - Barcelona vs Real Madrid 2018/19. A celebration of footballs fiercest rivalry, El Clásico. From stunning goals to unforgettable drama, we revisit the clashes that defined generations and shaped legends.

programme.title: El Clasico Legends: Ousmane Dembele
programme.desc: Ousmane Dembele. During his spell at Barcelona, Ousmane Dembele took part in six LaLiga Clásicos - nine in total - with a record of five wins and four defeats. But two of these fixtures will probably stand out above the rest.

programme.title: El Clasico Legends: Álvaro Arbeloa
programme.desc: Álvaro Arbeloa. Álvaro Arbeloa played a key role in Clásicos, where he was handed the unenviable task of defending the likes of Leo Messi, Neymar Jr, Alexis Sánchez or David Villa down his flank.

programme.title: El Clasico Legends: Gareth Bale
programme.desc: Gareth Bale. Gareth Bale played in LaLiga 11 Clásicos and 15 in total. And despite his numbers against Barcelona not being spectacular, he did score a memorable goal in the 2014 Copa del Rey final.
